  "texts": [
    "To provide a comprehensive evaluation for LLMs in multiagent cooperative task, results are formalized from two perspectives: (1) fundamental tool-usage and execution metrics that measure baseline proficiency of LLM agents (Table 3); and (2) two proposed novel cooperative metrics, Cooperative Tool Ratio (CT) and Self-Organization (SO), that capture autonomy and emergent coordination among agents (Table 4).",
    "Table 3 illustrates the fundamental capability of LLMs agents in Tool-RoCo, including tool usage, reflection, modification, and win under four cooperation paradigms.",
    "The results reveal a consistent tendency that larger LLMs exhibit stronger structured tool usage compared to smaller ones.",
    "For example, in the Cabinet task under the centralized paradigm, GPT-5 achieves over 93.04% tool-calling success with 75.90% execution validity, whereas GPT-4o-mini remains below 19.40% and 9.40%, respectively.",
    "This result illustrates a common: larger models enable the invocation of tools effectively and progress toward task goals."
  ],
